1.12.1.1.10:
Added:
/break Breaks the block you're looking at.
/spawn Teleports you to spawn.
/wild Teleports you randomly in the world.
/ptime <day/night/normal/6900> Sets your personal time, can be used on any server. I am not responsible if you get banned because of this.
1.12.1.1.11:
Added:
/smite <player> Strikes someone with lightning.
/through Teleports you through a wall.

Fixed:
All commands which you were supposed to be able to use on singleplayer or modded server not being able to use.
TL;DR a lot of permission issues.
1.12.1.1.12:
Added:
/hat Puts the item you're holding on your head.
/repair Repairs the item you're holding
/rename <name> Renames the item you're holding, you can use color codes like &1, &2, &3, etc.
1.12.1.1.13:
Added:
/powertool <command> Assigns a command to the item you're holding using NBT.
/resetnbt Resets the NBT data of the item you're holding.
/shownbt Shows the NBT data of the item you're holding.

Changes:
The mod is now usable for any Minecraft version ranging from 1.11 to 1.12.
1.12.1.1.14:
Added:
/vanish Makes you invisible, you basically get the invisibility potion effect but without the potion effect.
/setfov <fov> Sets your fov, client sided command.
/setrenderdistance <distance> Sets your render distance, client sided command.
/descend Teleports you down 1 floor.
/ascend Teleports you up 1 floor.
/optool Enchants whatever tool your holding with every enchantment of level 16348.
/superpickaxe Makes you able to destroy any block with any pickaxe.

Changed/fixed:
Some small things which I forgot what they were.
1.12.1.1.15:
Added:
/calc <equation> Calculates a math equation so you don't have to.
/optool Enchants the item you're holding with every enchantment of level 16348.

Changed:
The registering of the commands now looks a lot cleaner altough you won't notice this in-game.
1.12.1.1.15.1:
Fixed:
Game crashing when trying to break a block.
1.12.1.1.16:
Added:
/time fix <value> Fixes the time to the set amount.
/enchant <player> <id> [level] Same as the normal command but now you can enchant any item with any enchantment of any level.
/serverstatus Shows the server statuses of all mojang and minecraft servers. Client sided command.
/pastnames [player] Shows the past names of the given player, player defaults to you. Client sided command.
1.12.1.1.17:
Added:
/fireball Summons a fireball in the direction you're looking.
The ability to sit on stairs.
1.12.1.1.17.1:
Changed:
The arrow will now be removed once you dismount the chair or go sit on another one.
1.12.1.1.18:
Added:
/urban <search term> Lookup a word on urban dictionary.

Changed:
The mod can now be used on 1.12.1.
1.12.1.1.19:
Added:
/whereami Shows your coordinates.
/whois <player> Get all of a player's information, including their ip, you hackerman.
/compareips <player1> <player2> Compares the ip addresses of 2 players to see if an account is an alt account of someone.
1.12.1.1.20:
Added:
/n/narrate [message] Let the narrator narrate a message for you, just doing /narrate makes you able to let it narrate a whole novel. This command does not work on Minecraft versions below 1.12.

Changed:
A very, very lazy way of registering the commands so now whenever I create a new class I don't have to change initialize.java and it'll just get registered when I relog :D (it did take me numerous hours before I achieved this.)
If your game crashes whenever you updated to 1.20, just restart and there shouldn't be a problem.
